<section xml:id="notes-week-01">
  <title>Week 1: Vectors, Matrices, and Systems</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      Put a goal at the top of each lecture note. Below is just sample filler. 
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>Interpret vectors in <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m> geometrically and algebraically.</li>
      <li>Write systems of linear equations in matrix form.</li>
      <li>Use row reduction to solve linear systems.</li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="notes-week-01-definitions">
    <title>Definitions</title>

    <definition xml:id="def-vector-rn">
      <statement>
        <p>
          A <term>vector</term> in <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m> is an ordered list
          <m>\vec{v}=(v_1,v_2,\ldots,v_n)</m> of real numbers.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </definition>

    <definition xml:id="def-span">
      <statement>
        <p>
          The <term>span</term> of vectors
          <m>\vec{v}_1,\ldots,\vec{v}_k</m> in <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m> is the set of all
          linear combinations
          <md>
            \mathrm{span}\{\vec{v}_1,\ldots,\vec{v}_k\}
            =
            \{c_1\vec{v}_1+\cdots+c_k\vec{v}_k : c_1,\ldots,c_k \in \mathbb{R}\}.
          </md>
        </p>
      </statement>
    </definition>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="notes-week-01-main-result">
    <title>Main Result</title>

    <theorem xml:id="thm-systems-and-row-reduction">
      <title>Row Reduction Preserves Solutions</title>
      <statement>
        <p>
          If the augmented matrix of one linear system is obtained from another
          by elementary row operations, then the two systems have the same
          solution set.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <proof>
        <p>
          Each elementary row operation corresponds to replacing one equation by
          an equivalent equation or by an equation obtained from reversible
          algebraic operations. Therefore a vector satisfies the original system
          if and only if it satisfies the transformed system.
        </p>
      </proof>
    </theorem>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="notes-week-01-worked-example">
    <title>Worked Example</title>

    <example xml:id="ex-row-reduction-template">
      <title>A Template Row Reduction Example</title>
      <p>
        Consider the system whose augmented matrix is
        <md>
          \left[
          \begin{array}{ccc|c}
          1 &amp; 2 &amp; -1 &amp; 3\\
          2 &amp; 5 &amp; 1 &amp; 4
          \end{array}
          \right].
        </md>
        Replace this example with one aligned to your first week of class.
      </p>
    </example>
  </subsection>
</section>
